# Rebuild after code changes for update panel

After making any code changes that the user wants to test, **always run a Debug build**:

```bash
cd /Users/mohebanwari/development/Jot && xcodebuild -project Jot.xcodeproj -scheme Jot -configuration Debug build -allowProvisioningUpdates 2>&1 | tail -8
```

**Why:** Jot has a `BuildWatcherManager` (DEBUG only) that watches `Jot.debug.dylib` for changes. When the binary updates while the app is running, an **update panel appears at the bottom of the left sidebar** (above Trash/Settings). The user relaunches from there.

**Do NOT:**
- Kill or relaunch the app directly (per `feedback_no_relaunch_after_build.mdc`)
- Skip the build step after code changes
- Assume the user will build manually

**Flow:**
1. Make code changes
2. Run `xcodebuild` Debug build
3. Confirm `BUILD SUCCEEDED`
4. Tell user the build is ready — they'll see the update panel in the sidebar and relaunch when ready
